<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-working-example" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>A Simple Working Example</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>The second chapter demonstrates how the book can hold both explanatory text and lightweight technical content. This example shows that the pipeline can handle equations in Markdown and technical notation.</p>
  </introduction>

  <section xml:id="sec-technical-content">
    <title>Technical notation</title>
    <p>Inline math: <math>\vec{v} = (1,2,3)</math></p>
    <p>Displayed equations are also supported.</p>
    <equation>
      <math>\nabla \times \vec{F} = \left( \frac{\partial F_z}{\partial y} - \frac{\partial F_y}{\partial z}, \dots \right)</math>
    </equation>
    <p>This is intentionally simple, but it shows that the same source files can support both narrative writing and technical notation.</p>
  </section>
</chapter>
